<item>
            <title>[MATH-936] RandomDataGenerator#nextLong violates bounds</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-936</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I attached a test.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the underlying RandomGenerator returns 0.0, then nextLong returns Long.MIN_VALUE, although the lower bound is Long.MIN_VALUE+1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The javadoc of RandomGenerator#nextDouble does not clearly define, whether the result includes the lower border of 0.0 or not.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In java.util.Random it clearly defined as included: &quot;uniformly from the range 0.0d (inclusive) to 1.0d (exclusive)&quot;. And the existence of JDKRandomGenerator suggests, that RandomGenerator should have the same contract.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I tested with version 3.1.1 from mvnrepository&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
